Taking the spotlight this month is Qala, a special edition by @vespaindia, that transforms Indian motifs into motion, blending traditional storytelling with delicate craftsmanship.

#Grazialndia #KhushiKapoor #Khushi #MarchCover

Repost from @graziaindia and @khushikapoor 

Young, restless, and raring to go, Khushi Kapoor is turning on the charm one film at a time, and she’s just getting started.

New month, new mood—Grazia India’s March 2025 issue is here to set the tone. Everything from the fashion and beauty trends that will rule, the social media detox you didn’t know you needed, and the freshest takes on style and culture. Consider this your seasonal reset.

Taking the spotlight this month on the cover is Qala, a special edition by @vespaindia, that has its roots in an Indian art form and is set in motion with Italian style.

Khushi is wearing a mini dress @studiomoonray; earrings, bracelet, both @studioloveletter; pumps, @onitsukatigerindia

latestPosts.caption:
On the learning curve:
Talking about things she has learnt along the way, Kapoor says “approaching emotions with honesty” is the single most important thing to keep in mind as an actor. “You need to feel the emotions that your character is feeling and go through those same emotional beats, otherwise it just comes across a bit inauthentic. Also, to just take your time; sometimes, as new actors, you tend to rush and finish your dialogues quickly, and you forget to be more present in the moment.”

Taking the spotlight this month is Qala, a special edition by @vespaindia, where tradition gets a modern spin. Inspired by Indian art forms, its design is a seamless blend of heritage and innovation, turning cultural storytelling into movement.

Khushi is wearing a mini dress @studiomoonray; earrings, bracelet, both @studioloveletter
